  "text": "We therefore define (17), depending on the specific value of the metabolic reaction free energy barrier and the rate determining gene number for each species, This estimation shows that the optimal growth temperature (OGT) for a well-evolved mesophile species, should be quite close to the evolutionary temperature, which we assume to be its natural growth temperature. This is confirmed by many experimental observations [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
